FT  12 JUL 93 / World News in Brief: Bosnia's leaders outline plan to create
federation
Bosnia's collective presidency yesterday agreed the outline of a proposal to
create a federation out of the republic. The plan rejects the principle of
ethnic divisions and is likely to be turned down by the Serbs and Croats.
Serb leaders warned again at the weekend that the Moslems would be left with
nothing if they rejected a three-way partition on ethnic lines. Page 2
A journalist carrying a British passport was found dead at Sarajevo airport,
the Foreign Office said. The man, who had been shot, was not named.
